    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ærdæg" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>ærdæg</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>половина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>half</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(во второй части
                            сложных слов) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(in the second
                            part of the complex words) </note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сторона</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(во второй части сложных слов)
                            </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(in the second part of the
                            complex words) </note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>side</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">;</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">;</note>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ærdægmard</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>полумертвый</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>half dead</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ærdægax˳yr</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>полуученый</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>half learnt</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>недоучка</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>half-educated person</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Batraz... c ʼītījy ærdæg ratydta æmæ jæ jæ særyl cæværdta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Батраз оторвал половину глетчера и положил себе на голову</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Batraz tore a half of glacier and put it on his head</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ræǵawæn je ʽrdæg mæn, innæ ʽrdæg—dæw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>половина табуна моя, другая половина — твоя</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>one half of the herd is mine, the other is yours</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>bæx ærdæg xwærd fæccæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лошадь была наполовину съедена</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the horse was half eaten</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."
                            /><biblScope>16%l3%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>arda-</w>
                        <gloss><q>половина</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сторона’ с обычным наращением
                    -%ig%i (← *%iarda-ka%i-). Без наращения %iærd%i- со значением ‘сторона’
                    выступает во множестве производных и сложных слов: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ardæm"/> ‘сюда’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ūrdæm"/>
                    ‘туда’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_alyrdæm"/> ‘во все стороны’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_fæjnærdæm"/> ‘в разные стороны’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wælærdæm"/> ‘вверх’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dælærdæm"
                    /> ‘вниз’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_falærdæm"/> ‘на ту сторону’, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_acyrdæm"/> ‘на эту сторону’ и др.; ср. также <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ærdæbon"/> ‘давеча’. Слово хорошо представлено в
                    индоиранских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(в сложных словах) </note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">(in complex words)
                        </note><w>*-ardak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>*-ard(ʼrδ)</w>
                        <gloss><q>сторона</q></gloss></mentioned> (%i*wīspard-%i = <mentioned
                        xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>alyrdæm</w>
                        <gloss><q>во все стороны</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>biśśi hālaa</w></mentioned> id.), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>hālaa</w></mentioned> (из *%iardaka%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>alak</w></mentioned> (из *%iardak%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-turfan"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽārag</w></mentioned> (<bibl/>%bМО XV 205)%b, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>arəδa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ardha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>половина</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сторона’.— <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>ord</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">'Seite'</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">'Seiteˈ</note>
                        <gloss><q>Umgebung</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"
                            ><w>ordö</w>
                        <gloss><q>zu</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>ordyn</w>
                        <gloss><q>bei</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. (<bibl/>%bW i е d е m а n n.
                    Syrjänisch-Deutsches Wörterbuch 209%b), возможно, усвоено из скифского. Более
                    широкое распространение получило в других иранских языках синонимическое слово
                    *%inaima%i-, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>aδara.naemat</w></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>dælærdygæj</w>
                        <gloss><q>снизу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>upara.naеmat</w></mentioned> =<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>wælærdygæj</w>
                        <gloss><q>сверху</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 77</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><author>%bGr.%b</author><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>arda-</w>
                        <gloss><q>half</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘side’ with a regular augmentation
                    -%ig%i (← *%iarda-ka%i-). Without augmentation, %iærd%i- as ‘half’ is found in a
                    number of derivates and complex words: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardæm"/>
                    'hither’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ūrdæm"/> ‘thither, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_alyrdæm"/> ‘towards all directions’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_fæjnærdæm"/> ‘towards different directions’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wælærdæm"/> ‘up’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dælærdæm"/>
                    ‘down’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_falærdæm"/> ‘on that side’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_acyrdæm"/> ‘on this side’ and others; compare also <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ærdæbon"/> ‘recently’. The word is well presented
                    in Indoiranian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(в сложных словах) </note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">(in complex words)
                        </note><w>*-ardak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>*-ard(ʼrδ)</w>
                        <gloss><q>side</q></gloss></mentioned> (%i*wīspard-%i = <mentioned
                        xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>alyrdæm</w>
                        <gloss><q>towards all directions</q></gloss></mentioned>, compare <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>biśśi hālaa</w></mentioned> id.), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>hālaa</w></mentioned> (from *%iardaka%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>alak</w></mentioned> (from *%iardak%i), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="pal-x-turfan"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽārag</w></mentioned> (<bibl/>%bМО XV 205)%b, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>arəδa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ardha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>half</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘side’.— <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>ord</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">'Seite'</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">'Seiteˈ</note>
                        <gloss><q>Umgebung</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"
                            ><w>ordö</w>
                        <gloss><q>zu</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>ordyn</w>
                        <gloss><q>bei</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.
                            (<bibl><author>Wiedemann</author><biblScope>Syrjänisch-Deutsches
                            Wörterbuch 209</biblScope></bibl>), possibly comes from Scythian. More
                    widespread in other Iranian languages is the synonymous word *%inaima%i-, ср.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>aδara.naemat</w></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>dælærdygæj</w>
                        <gloss><q>underneath</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>upara.naеmat</w></mentioned> =<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>wælærdygæj</w>
                        <gloss><q>above</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 77</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><author>%bGr.%b</author><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
